'''Renegade Flight''' was a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] unit under the leadership of [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Arhul Narra/Legends|Arhul Narra]]. It was assigned to the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command]] Headquarters before its destruction in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]] at the [[Battle of Derra IV]].

==History==
[[File:Renegades.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Narra and a Renegade Flight pilot in an Imperial ambush over Derra IV]]
Renegade Flight was one of the oldest [[Starfighter/Legends|fighter]] groups in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance]], with a service history dating back before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. It was named for the [[Incom Corporation/Legends|Incom Corporation]] design team that defected to the Alliance early in the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Military lore had it that one of Renegade Flight's fighters dated back to the original [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] prototypes. Renegade Flight was led by [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Arhul Narra/Legends|Arhul Narra]], a veteran [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] nicknamed "Boss" by other members of the [[Squadron/Legends|squadron]]. The squadron was key to the early Alliance victory at the [[Battle of Ton-Falk]], exploiting an ingeniously simple tactic suggested by [[Renegade Leader]] Narra's [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[K-3PO/Legends|K-3PO]] to destroy two [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Frigate/Legends|frigates]] and a [[Dreadnaught/Legends|dreadnaught]].<ref name="GG3" />

Following the Battle of Yavin, Renegade Flight was integrated into [[Red Squadron (Rebel Alliance)/Legends|Red Squadron]], which was reconstituted as a pair of flights, Narra's Renegades and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Flight]].<ref name="EGTW" /> Narra and Renegade Flight were assigned to the [[Alliance High Command/Legends|Alliance High Command]] group, tasked with protecting the Alliance transport [[Convoy/Legends|convoys]] that supplied High Command's constantly moving headquarters.<ref name="GG3" />

Before the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]]<ref name="GG3" /> in [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> Renegade Flight was escorting a supply convoy to [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] when the convoy was [[Battle of Derra IV|ambushed]] in [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]] over [[Derra IV/Legends|Derra IV]] by an Imperial force led by the [[181st Imperial Fighter Wing/Legends|181st Imperial Fighter Wing]] attached to an [[Ton-Falk-class escort carrier|''Ton-Falk''-class escort carrier]]. All the Rebel [[Transport/Legends|transports]] were destroyed and every member of Renegade Flight, including [[Ketku]] and "[[Renegade Three]]," was killed. Ironically, the [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ship]] design that launched the fighters that destroyed Renegade Flight was developed as a result of the Renegades' victory at [[Ton-Falk]]. A plaque commemorating the lost pilots hung on the command deck of the Rebel frigate, [[Chancellor (frigate)|''Chancellor'']],<ref name="GG3" /> while Skywalker and [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] expanded Rogue Flight to a full squadron to fill the gap left by the loss of the Renegades.<ref name="EGTW" />

==Behind the scenes==
The ''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' and ''[[Who's Who in Rogue Squadron]]'' place Commander Narra and Renegade Flight at the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Lucasfilm's Leland Chee has since confirmed this as an error on the [[StarWars.com]] forums.<ref name="SWB">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=222689&start=3000#15740050|thread=Books, Comics, & Television VIPs|user=[[Leland Chee|Tasty Taste]]|date=2006-10-05|time=9:45 AM}}</ref>

